From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 15:20:00 +0200
Subject: soundwire: qcom: only reject over-declared port counts

Since commit 9e53a66a2f2f ("soundwire: qcom: deprecate qcom,din/out-ports")
the controller reads the port count from SWRM_COMP_PARAMS and treats the
qcom,din-ports/qcom,dout-ports properties as an optional override that is
still honoured (num_*_ports = val). A device tree describing only the ports
a board actually wires, fewer than the controller exposes, is therefore a
valid configuration.

That commit changed the guard from "val > count" to "val != count" and
dropped the -EINVAL, so every board that describes a subset now logs a
spurious error at probe, e.g. on SC8280XP swr1 which the SoC dtsi has always
declared as 5 dout / 0 din:

  din-ports (0) mismatch with controller (1)
  dout-ports (5) mismatch with controller (6)

Only over-declaration is actually invalid: requesting more ports than the
controller has would set up ports that do not exist. Restore the original
guard, reject val > count with -EINVAL and accept any subset silently.

Fixes: 9e53a66a2f2f ("soundwire: qcom: deprecate qcom,din/out-ports")
Signed-off-by: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
---
 drivers/soundwire/qcom.c | 14 ++++++----
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/soundwire/qcom.c b/drivers/soundwire/qcom.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/soundwire/qcom.c
+++ b/drivers/soundwire/qcom.c
@@ -1425,20 +1425,22 @@ static int qcom_swrm_get_port_config(struct qcom_swrm_ctrl *ctrl)
 	ctrl->num_din_ports = FIELD_GET(SWRM_COMP_PARAMS_DIN_PORTS_MASK, val);
 
 	ret = of_property_read_u32(np, "qcom,din-ports", &val);
-	if (!ret) { /* only if present */
-		if (val != ctrl->num_din_ports) {
-			dev_err(ctrl->dev, "din-ports (%d) mismatch with controller (%d)",
+	if (!ret) { /* deprecated, honoured only if present */
+		if (val > ctrl->num_din_ports) {
+			dev_err(ctrl->dev, "din-ports (%d) exceed controller count (%d)\n",
 				val, ctrl->num_din_ports);
+			return -EINVAL;
 		}
 
 		ctrl->num_din_ports = val;
 	}
 
 	ret = of_property_read_u32(np, "qcom,dout-ports", &val);
-	if (!ret) { /* only if present */
-		if (val != ctrl->num_dout_ports) {
-			dev_err(ctrl->dev, "dout-ports (%d) mismatch with controller (%d)",
+	if (!ret) { /* deprecated, honoured only if present */
+		if (val > ctrl->num_dout_ports) {
+			dev_err(ctrl->dev, "dout-ports (%d) exceed controller count (%d)\n",
 				val, ctrl->num_dout_ports);
+			return -EINVAL;
 		}
 
 		ctrl->num_dout_ports = val;
